Here are the user stories derived from the Python code:

1. As a data administrator, I want to process deletions for a specific date, so that I can maintain data accuracy and compliance.  
2. As a system logger, I want to log deletion processing activities, so that troubleshooting and auditing are easier.  
3. As a UI designer, I want to redesign a page with new styles, so that the user interface remains modern and user-friendly.  
4. As a UX researcher, I want to generate user testing reports for agencies, so that we can document feedback and improve the system.  
5. As a test coordinator, I want to schedule user testing with advanced notice, so that testers are prepared and available.  
6. As a FABS administrator, I want to update FABS submissions when publish status changes, so that submissions reflect their current state accurately.  
7. As a FABS administrator, I want to prevent double publishing of FABS submissions, so that data integrity is maintained.  
8. As a FABS processor, I want to derive necessary fields for FABS submissions, so that submissions are complete and formatted correctly.  
9. As a file processor, I want to generate D files with caching, so that duplicate files are not created unnecessarily.  
10. As a validation engineer, I want to load validation rules from a database, so that rules are up-to-date and configurable.  
11. As a FABS validator, I want to validate FABS submissions with updated rules, so that only compliant data is processed.  
12. As a data loader, I want to load historical FABS data with FREC derivations, so that historical records are complete and accurate.  
13. As a data loader, I want to load historical FPDS data from both sources, so that we have comprehensive historical records.  
14. As a system administrator, I want to execute all implemented user stories in sequence, so that the system functions as an integrated whole.

            UXResearcher(),

            FABSAdmin(),
            FABSProcessor(),
